3 rd Project Documentaions and Tips
------------------------------------

-> Requirment
	-> Registration Page
		user need to enter below fields 
		-> Full Name
		-> email
		-> Phone
		-> Gender
		-> DOb
		-> SSN
		
	-> Activation Page
		-> Email
		-> old Password
		-> New Password
		-> conform Password
	
	-> Login Page
		-> Email
		-> password (forgot password)
		
	-> view All Details
		-> Full Name
		-> email
		-> Phone
		-> Gender
		-> DOb
		-> SSN
		-> delete
		-> edit
		-> softdelete
	
	-> Forgot Password
		-> password should send to user Email

- step - 1
----------
	-> Here We neeed one table of USER_MASTER
		-> USER_ID
		-> USER_NAME
		-> USER_EMAIL
		-> USER_PASS
		-> USER_PHONE
		-> USER_DOB
		-> USER_GENDER
		-> USER_SSN
		-> ACC_STATUS
		-> DELETED
		-> CREATED_AT
		-> UPDATED_AT
		-> CREATED_BY
		-> UPDATED_BY
		
- step - 2
----------
	-> create Spring Boot stater Poject with following dependiendy
		-> spring-web
		-> spring-data-jpa
		-> mysqlDriver
		-> java-mail-sender
		-> lombok
		-> spring-dev-Tools
	
	-> Create a userMaster Entity Class with above mentioned properties
	
	-> create seperate Binding Classes for every request and response objects (like entity)
		-> User 
			-> String fullName
			-> String email
			-> LocalDate dob
			-> String phone
			-> String gender
			-> String ssn
		-> ActiveAcc
			-> String email
			-> oldPass
			-> newPass
			-> conformPass
		-> LogIn
			-> String email
			-> String pass
	
	-> create Service Interface 
		-> Public boolean Save(User user)
		-> Public List<User> getAllUsers();
		-> public User findUserById(Integer id)
		-> public boolean deleteUserById(integer id)
		-> public String activateUser(Integer id , String status)
		-> public User findUserByEmail(String email)
		-> public String login(Login login)
		-> public boolean forgotPassword(String email);
	
		
